Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great enthusiasm that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Development Engineer II* position with *AWS CloudFront Console*. I bring over three years of professional engineering experience building production AI-agent systems, agentic console surfaces, and distributed backend infrastructure — along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate with a 4.0 GPA from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience at Sperse and Qualitest, I have built and shipped systems that directly reflect the agentic and distributed infrastructure depth this role demands. At Sperse, I engineered a FastMCP-based MCP server — the agent experience (AX) layer implementing tool-use protocols (MCP and function calling) — exposing 160+ tool-callable actions to first- and third-party AI agents over a multi-tenant backend with OpenTelemetry instrumentation and tenant-aware access control; this mirrors exactly the AX layer work central to the CloudFront Console team's mission. Alongside it, I architected a multi-agent autonomous planning platform using LangGraph, LangChain, and FastAPI with LLM integration that decomposes customer goals and routes 10,000+ requests across 40+ specialized sub-agents — the same autonomous-decomposition-into-validated-operations pattern your team is building at AWS edge scale. I also built an agentic console experience using React and TypeScript with React Flow that lets users design, execute, and observe agent swarms in real time backed by Temporal for durable execution and Redis for live progress tracking, and integrated LlamaIndex-powered RAG agents that surface answers to natural-language questions grounded in live technical documentation. To keep these systems production-ready, I built GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines with OpenTelemetry trace-based eval suites gating every deploy by scoring latency, tool-call accuracy, and safety across distributed environments. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I orchestrated long-running distributed jobs with AWS Step Functions and Lambda across 100K+ weekly executions with end-to-end CloudWatch observability, and designed a distributed Storage Service in Java and Spring Boot spanning AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO — hands-on experience building reliable multi-tiered systems at cloud scale. Together, these roles have prepared me to build, ship, and operate the intelligent agentic surface the CloudFront Console team is constructing.

My personal project, Dark Factory — a distributed coding-agent orchestrator in Elixir and TypeScript — further reflects my thinking about autonomous multi-machine systems: it decomposes large coding requests into dependency-aware task DAGs and executes them across agents with autonomous retry, timeout handling, and failure recovery. Building it reinforced the evidence-over-opinion, ownership-over-delegation principles that resonate with your team's engineering culture, and deepened my conviction that the shift from static configuration consoles to intelligent, agentic surfaces is the defining infrastructure transformation of this era.

I have always been passionate about *customer obsession* and *passion for invention* — the core principles that drive AWS — and envision myself contributing to the mission of reinventing how customers interact with CloudFront, WAF, and Shield by building the intelligent agentic console that replaces manual configuration workflows. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

